title: Interactive Google map shows your city’s most popular Halloween costume
text: Are you still looking for a Halloween costume and are worried that lots of people have already taken your favorite ideas? Well worry not: An interactive map powered by Google Trends called Frightgeist can tell you which costume searches are the most popular ones in your city. FROM EARLIER: Watch Michael J. Fox show off Nike’s self-lacing shoes on Kimmel As you can see in the photo at the top of the page, Daenerys Targaryen of Game of Thrones fame is a popular costume in Alpena, Michigan. Here are some popular costumes in the major American cities: Boston: Pirate Philadelphia: Harley Quinn New York City: Superhero Miami: Harley Quinn Atlanta: Pirate New Orleans: Pirate Milwaukee: Star Wars Denver: Star Wars Seattle: Harley Quinn Dallas: »
